    <div xml:id="PN233">
      <lg type="edition" style="pūṭṭuvil">
<l>poyyā kiyarō poyyā kiyarō</l>
<l>pāvaṭi yāṉaip paricilark karukāc</l>
<l>cīrkeḻu nōṉṟā ḷakutaikaṭ ṭōṉṟiya</l>
<l>poṉpuṉai tikiriyiṟ poyyā kiyarō</l>
<l>virumpā ṇokkaṟ ṟalaivaṉ perumpūṭ</l>
<l>pōraṭu tāṉai yevvi mārpi</l>
<l>ṉeḵkuṟu viḻuppuṇ palaveṉa</l>
<l>vaikuṟu viṭiya liyampiya kuralē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>  Let it be a lie! Let it be a lie! (1)</l>
<l>Like the gold-made discus (4ab)</l>
<l>that appeared before the eye of Akutai of excellent durable effort (3)</l>
<l>who is not scarce to mendicants with large-footed elephants, (2)</l>
<l>	let it be a lie</l>
<l>– the voice that anounced at the crack of dawn (8)</l>
<l>that the excellent wound caused by a blade are many (7)</l>
<l>on the chest of Evvi, with a army killing in battle, (6)</l>
<l>with big ornaments, leader of a big clan of bards. (5)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
